h2 Using Dropdowns
p.-text
  | A dropdown must be associated to an activator, commonly a button, which, at the time of being clicked, expands
  | the dropdown. Activator and dropdown should be contained in a div with an <code>m-dropdown</code> class, or otherwise, the
  | activator must reference the dropdown with a <code>data-target</code> attribute.
p.-text
  | Use the <code>m-dropdown__trigger</code> class on your activator button to make the chevron appear.
h3 Example 1
p.-text
  | Trigger and dropdown enclosed in the same div.
ul#a-tabs--expanded.a-tabs
  li.-active
    a(href='#a-tabs-panel--expanded-false') Initial
  li
    a(href='#a-tabs-panel--expanded-true') Expanded
.example.-mb--3
  #a-tabs-panel--expanded-false.a-tabs-panel.-active
    .-p--3
      .m-dropdown(style='margin-bottom: 7rem')
        button.a-btn.m-dropdown__trigger Dropdown component
        .m-dropdown__menu
          a.m-dropdown__menu-item(href='#') Element 1
          a.m-dropdown__menu-item(href='#') Element 2
          a.m-dropdown__menu-item(href='#') Element 3
    :code(lang="html")
      <div class="m-dropdown">
        <button class="a-btn m-dropdown__trigger">Dropdown component</button>
        <div class="m-dropdown__menu">
          <a class="m-dropdown__menu-item" href="#">Element 1</a>
          <a class="m-dropdown__menu-item" href="#">Element 2</a>
